LME Aluminum, Cobalt, Tin Margins to Change, LCH Clearnet Says

-- B y   A g n i e s z k a   T r o s z k i e w i c z
-- 
2011-04-15T16:26:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-15/lme-aluminum-cobalt-tin-margins-to-change-lch-clearnet-says.html
Margins will fall for aluminum and
cobalt traded on the London Metal Exchange and rise for tin, LCH
Clearnet Ltd. said.  Margins for high-grade aluminum will drop to $155 a metric
ton from $165, and cobalt margins will decline to $3,000 a ton
from $3,400, the clearing house said today on its website.
Margins for tin will increase to $2,100 a ton from $1,900. The
changes take effect after trading ends on April 20, said LCH
Clearnet,  Europe â€™s biggest clearing house.  To contact the reporter on this story:
